<p>I have Customer XML with date-time fields but sometimes there are only dates. I need a result with only date-time fields and no date fields. (The xml I work with hat much more fields and is nested)</p>  <p>I thinks there is a better way then my brute force attempt. </p>  <pre><code>xml = "&lt;root&gt;&lt;date&gt;2003-07-15T10:00:00&lt;/date&gt;&lt;enddate&gt;2016-02-02&lt;/enddate&gt;&lt;startdate&gt;2000-02-10&lt;/startdate&gt;&lt;/root&gt;"; string result = string.Empty; if (!string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(xml)) {   XDocument doc = XDocument.Parse(xml);   string xml1 = doc.ToString();   Regex rgx = new Regex(@"&gt;(\d{4}-\d\d-\d\d)&lt;/");   result = rgx.Replace(xml1, "&gt;$1T00:00:00&lt;/"); } </code></pre>